{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "cvh-client-api-2026-05-08",
    "name": "CryptoVaultHub Client API",
    "description": "Sequência completa de integração validada na homologação 2026-05-08 (BSC mainnet, projeto BrPay, 13/13 PASS).\n\nUse o Collection Runner para executar do começo ao fim — variáveis (projectId, depositAddress, withdrawalId) propagam automaticamente entre as requests via test scripts.\n\n**Antes de rodar:**\n1. Ajuste `apiKey` em Variables.\n2. Os passos com `[USER ACTION]` na descrição exigem ação fora do Postman (enviar BNB, etc.).\n3. Os passos `Wait …` rodam um único polling — re-execute manualmente até atingir o estado terminal, ou use o Runner com `iterationCount` ≥ 30 e `delay` de 8000ms.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "https://api.vaulthub.live/client/v1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "apiKey",
      "value": "cvh_live_REPLACE_ME",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Sua API key. Portal → Sidebar → API Keys."
    },
    {
      "key": "chainId",
      "value": "56",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Chain ID alvo. 56 = BSC mainnet."
    },
    {
      "key": "tokenSymbol",
      "value": "BNB",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "withdrawalAmount",
      "value": "0.001",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "sourceWallet",
      "value": "hot",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Source of funds: 'hot' (default, multisig) or 'gas_tank' (EOA, native-only)."
    },
    {
      "key": "withdrawalTarget",
      "value": "0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Endereço EVM externo. Edite antes de rodar o passo 9."
    },
    {
      "key": "externalId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Preenchido automaticamente no passo 5."
    },
    {
      "key": "projectId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Preenchido automaticamente no passo 1."
    },
    {
      "key": "webhookId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Preenchido automaticamente no passo 4."
    },
    {
      "key": "depositAddress",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Preenchido automaticamente no passo 5."
    },
    {
      "key": "withdrawalId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Preenchido automaticamente no passo 10."
    },
    {
      "key": "idempotencyKey",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Gerado automaticamente no passo 10."
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      {
        "key": "key",
        "value": "X-API-Key",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "value",
        "value": "{{apiKey}}",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "in",
        "value": "header",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Setup",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Resolve project (smoke test)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('payload has projects[]', () => pm.expect(j.projects).to.be.an('array').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('projectId', j.projects[0].id);",
                  "console.log('captured projectId =', j.projects[0].id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/projects",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "projects"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Confirma que a API key é válida e retorna o projeto que ela escopa. Captura `projectId`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List wallets",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const chain = parseInt(pm.collectionVariables.get('chainId'), 10);",
                  "const types = j.wallets.filter(w => w.chainId === chain).map(w => w.walletType);",
                  "pm.test('hot wallet exists for chain', () => pm.expect(types).to.include('hot'));",
                  "pm.test('gas_tank wallet exists for chain', () => pm.expect(types).to.include('gas_tank'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/wallets",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "wallets"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Verifica que existem hot wallet + gas tank na chain alvo. Sem isso, depósito/saque não funcionam."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Confirm gas tank status",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('gas tank not critical', () => pm.expect(['ok', 'warning']).to.include(j.status));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/gas-tanks/{{chainId}}",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "gas-tanks",
                "{{chainId}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Saque exige gas tank ok. Critical → pare e refunde."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Webhook (opcional)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register webhook",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('webhookId', j.id || j.webhook?.id);",
                  "if (j.secret) console.log('Webhook secret (guarde!):', j.secret);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"url\": \"https://webhook.site/REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_RECEIVER\",\n  \"events\": [\n    \"deposit.detected\",\n    \"deposit.confirmed\",\n    \"deposit.swept\",\n    \"withdrawal.submitted\",\n    \"withdrawal.confirmed\",\n    \"withdrawal.failed\"\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/webhooks",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "webhooks"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Registra um receptor de webhooks. Guarde o `secret` retornado — você usa pra verificar HMAC-SHA256 nos payloads."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Deposit",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Generate deposit address",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Gera externalId único por execução do Runner",
                  "const id = `customer-${Date.now()}`;",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('externalId', id);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const addr = j.depositAddress?.address || j.address;",
                  "pm.test('address returned', () => pm.expect(addr).to.match(/^0x[a-fA-F0-9]{40}$/));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('depositAddress', addr);",
                  "console.log('depositAddress =', addr);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"externalId\": \"{{externalId}}\",\n  \"label\": \"Postman test deposit\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/wallets/{{chainId}}/deposit-address",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "wallets",
                "{{chainId}}",
                "deposit-address"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Gera endereço determinístico (CREATE2 forwarder). Idempotente por `externalId`. O contrato é deployado lazy no primeiro depósito."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "[USER ACTION] Send funds",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "console.log('==============================================');",
                  "console.log('Envie fundos (chain', pm.collectionVariables.get('chainId'), ') para:');",
                  "console.log('  ', pm.collectionVariables.get('depositAddress'));",
                  "console.log('Depois siga para o passo \"Wait deposit swept\" e re-execute até status=swept.');",
                  "console.log('==============================================');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Placeholder. Em produção o usuário final envia BNB/ETH/USDT pra `{{depositAddress}}` a partir do app dele. Esta request só faz um GET /health pra registrar o ponto no Runner."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Wait deposit swept (poll)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const addr = pm.collectionVariables.get('depositAddress').toLowerCase();",
                  "const dep = j.deposits.find(d => (d.address || d.depositAddress || '').toLowerCase() === addr);",
                  "if (!dep) {",
                  "  console.log('Depósito ainda não detectado. Re-execute em ~10s.');",
                  "  pm.test('deposit row exists', () => pm.expect(dep).to.not.be.undefined);",
                  "  return;",
                  "}",
                  "console.log('deposit status =', dep.status, ' txHash =', dep.txHash);",
                  "pm.test('terminal status reached', () => pm.expect(['confirmed', 'sweep_pending', 'swept']).to.include(dep.status));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/deposits?limit=20&page=1",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "deposits"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "20"
                },
                {
                  "key": "page",
                  "value": "1"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Polling do estado do depósito. Cada execução é uma checagem; em produção use webhooks. Estados: pending → confirmed → sweep_pending → swept."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify hot wallet has funds",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const native = j.balances?.find(b => b.isNative) || j.balances?.[0];",
                  "console.log('hot wallet balance:', native?.balanceFormatted || native?.balance);",
                  "pm.test('balance > 0', () => pm.expect(parseFloat(native?.balance || '0')).to.be.greaterThan(0));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/wallets/{{chainId}}/balances",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "wallets",
                "{{chainId}}",
                "balances"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Confirma que o sweep depositou os fundos na hot wallet."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Withdrawal",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Whitelist withdrawal target",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// 201 = criou, 409 = já existe (também ok)",
                  "pm.test('201 ou 409 (already whitelisted)', () => pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  console.log('whitelisted address id =', j.address?.id || j.id);",
                  "  console.log('cooldown ends at =', j.address?.cooldownExpiresAt || j.cooldownExpiresAt);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"address\": \"{{withdrawalTarget}}\",\n  \"chainId\": {{chainId}},\n  \"label\": \"Postman test target\",\n  \"notes\": \"Adicionado via Postman runner\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/addresses",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "addresses"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Whitelist obrigatório antes de saque. Novos endereços têm cooldown de 24h — saque imediato vai falhar com 422 enquanto não vencer."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create withdrawal",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const idem = `wd-${pm.collectionVariables.get('externalId') || 'manual'}-${Date.now()}`;",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('idempotencyKey', idem);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const wd = j.withdrawal?.withdrawal || j.withdrawal || j;",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('withdrawalId', wd.id);",
                  "console.log('withdrawalId =', wd.id, ' status =', wd.status);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"chainId\": {{chainId}},\n  \"tokenSymbol\": \"{{tokenSymbol}}\",\n  \"toAddress\": \"{{withdrawalTarget}}\",\n  \"amount\": \"{{withdrawalAmount}}\",\n  \"memo\": \"Postman test withdrawal\",\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"{{idempotencyKey}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/withdrawals",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "withdrawals"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Cria o saque. Estado inicial = pending_approval. Em modo full-custody, próximo passo é o self-approve."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create withdrawal (gas tank)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const idem = `wd-gt-${Date.now()}`;",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('idempotencyKey', idem);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const wd = j.withdrawal?.withdrawal || j.withdrawal || j;",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('withdrawalId', wd.id);",
                  "console.log('gas_tank withdrawalId =', wd.id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"chainId\": {{chainId}},\n  \"sourceWallet\": \"gas_tank\",\n  \"tokenSymbol\": \"{{tokenSymbol}}\",\n  \"toAddress\": \"{{withdrawalTarget}}\",\n  \"amount\": \"{{withdrawalAmount}}\",\n  \"memo\": \"Postman gas-tank test\",\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"{{idempotencyKey}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/withdrawals",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "withdrawals"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Variant of 'Create withdrawal' that explicitly uses sourceWallet='gas_tank'. Token is forced to the chain native by the API regardless of what is sent. The 422 errors specific to this path are: 'Gas Tank source only supports the chain native token' and 'Insufficient gas tank balance after reserve' (reserve = 2 × platform_topup_amount_wei)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Self-approve (full-custody)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 OK', () => pm.expect([200, 201]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const wd = j.withdrawal?.withdrawal || j.withdrawal || j;",
                  "pm.test('status approved', () => pm.expect(wd.status).to.equal('approved'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/withdrawals/{{withdrawalId}}/approve",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "withdrawals",
                "{{withdrawalId}}",
                "approve"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Em full-custody, a API key já tem autoridade total — este passo apenas avança o estado de pending_approval para approved. O cron worker pega no próximo tick (≤ 30s)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Wait withdrawal confirmed (poll)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const wd = j.withdrawal?.withdrawal || j.withdrawal || j;",
                  "console.log('withdrawal status =', wd.status, ' txHash =', wd.txHash);",
                  "if (wd.txHash) console.log('BSCScan:', `https://bscscan.com/tx/${wd.txHash}`);",
                  "pm.test('terminal status', () => pm.expect(['broadcasting', 'confirmed', 'failed', 'rejected']).to.include(wd.status));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/withdrawals/{{withdrawalId}}",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "withdrawals",
                "{{withdrawalId}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Polling do estado do saque. Re-execute até status = confirmed ou failed/rejected. Em produção, escute o webhook withdrawal.confirmed."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Cleanup",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Delete webhook (opcional)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('204 ou 200', () => pm.expect([200, 204]).to.include(pm.response.code));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/webhooks/{{webhookId}}",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "webhooks",
                "{{webhookId}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Limpeza do receptor de teste."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Self-service API key management",
      "description": "Endpoints reachable from a logged-in portal session (JWT cookie). Cannot be exercised with an API key — they are guarded by JwtOnlyAuthGuard to prevent privilege escalation.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List my API keys",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "",
                "disabled": true,
                "description": "Disabled: this endpoint is JWT-only and rejects X-API-Key (privilege escalation block)."
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api-keys",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api-keys"
              ]
            },
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{portalJwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "## Authentication: JWT-only (portal session)\nThis endpoint REJECTS X-API-Key with 401. Use a portal session JWT instead.\n\n### How to obtain `{{portalJwt}}`\n1. Log in at https://portal.vaulthub.live\n2. Open DevTools → Application → Cookies → `cvh_session` → copy the value (or the access token from /auth/me)\n3. In the Postman environment, set `portalJwt` = that value.\n\n### Why JWT-only\nAPI key creation must require human-confirmed authentication so a leaked API key cannot mint new keys with broader scopes (privilege escalation block, security redesign 2026-05-09)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create API key",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-API-Key",
                "value": "",
                "disabled": true,
                "description": "Disabled: this endpoint is JWT-only and rejects X-API-Key (privilege escalation block)."
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"projectId\": 1,\n  \"scopes\": [\"wallets:read\", \"forwarders:flush\"],\n  \"label\": \"Postman test\",\n  \"ipAllowlist\": [\"203.0.113.0/24\"],\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2026-12-31T23:59:59Z\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api-keys",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api-keys"
              ]
            },
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{portalJwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
